    <h4>Description:</h4>
    <p>Corn Chaat is a tangy and spicy Indian snack made with boiled sweet corn, spices, herbs, and lemon juice. It's quick, healthy, and super delicious!</p>

    <h4>Prep Time:</h4>
    <p>‚è±Ô∏è <strong>10 minutes</strong></p>

    <h4>Ingredients:</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>1 cup sweet corn (boiled)</li>
        <li>1 small onion (finely chopped)</li>
        <li>1 tomato (finely chopped)</li>
        <li>1 green chili (chopped)</li>
        <li>1 tbsp lemon juice</li>
        <li>1/2 tsp chaat masala</li>
        <li>1/4 tsp red chili powder</li>
        <li>Salt to taste</li>
        <li>Chopped coriander leaves</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Instructions:</h4>
    <ol>
        <li>In a bowl, mix boiled sweet corn, onion, tomato, and green chili.</li>
        <li>Add chaat masala, red chili powder, salt, and lemon juice.</li>
        <li>Mix everything well and garnish with coriander leaves.</li>
        <li>Serve immediately for best flavor and crunch.</li>
    </ol>
